14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-189.3 of Title 70, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. For this section, "special education administrator" means
19 the director and assistant director of a special education program
20 for a school district.
21 B. Beginning August 1, 2026, no school district shall employ a
22 special education administrator unless the individual:
23 1. Holds a valid standard teaching certificate issued by the
24 State Board of Education; and
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2702 Page 1

1 2. Except as provided for in paragraph 2 of subsection D of
2 this section, obtains an acknowledgment of competency as provided
3 for in subsection C within one (1) year of being employed as a
4 special education administrator.
5 C. 1. The State Board of Education shall issue an
6 acknowledgement of competency in the area of special education
7 federal and state laws, regulations, policies, and procedures to a
8 special education administrator. By January 1, 2026, the State
9 Board shall develop two (2) tracks for completing a one-time
10 acknowledgement of competency:
11 a. a micro-credential track for individuals with five (5)
12 or less years of experience previously or currently
13 serving in the role of a special education
14 administrator, and
15 b. a standard track for individuals who are not required
16 to obtain the micro-credential and have six (6) or
17 more years of experience currently serving in the role
18 of a special education administrator.
19 2. The content of the 150-clock hour special education program
20 shall be the same for the standard track and the micro-credential
21 track, except the micro-credential track shall require mastery of
22 competency at or above seventy percent (70%) on coursework and
23 examinations.
24
