1 3. Beginning August 1, 2026, an individual must complete either
2 the standard or micro-credential track within one (1) calendar year
3 from the date of hire.
4 4. At the successful completion of either the standard or
5 micro-credential track, the individual shall receive a certificate
6 of completion which will be maintained as part of the employee's
7 record with the local education agency and stored in the Oklahoma
8 Educator Credentialing System.
9 D. 1. Except as provided in paragraph 2 of this subsection, a
10 special education administrator shall successfully complete the
11 subject area competency examination in either mild-moderate
12 disabilities, severe-profound disabilities, or comprehensive special
13 education as prescribed by the State Department of Education.
14 2. An individual who has a valid Special Education Teaching
15 Certificate as provided for in Sections 6-122.7, 6-122.8, or 6-122.9
16 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes or an individual who has a
17 master's degree in school administration, special education, or a
18 related field shall be exempt from the acknowledgement of competency
19 requirement in subsection C of this section and the subject area
20 competency examination requirement in paragraph 1 of this
21 subsection.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
